name: FoodCartMicroservice
description: This project is built using a microservices architecture. The goal is to create a scalable, maintainable, and easily deployable application that handles various aspects of an Food Cart system. The architecture utilizes Core Java, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Netflix Eureka, Spring Cloud Gateway, OpenFiegn and other technologies to achieve this.

name: Clinic-System
description: The Clinic Management Microservices project is designed to streamline clinic operations by efficiently managing patient information and payments across multiple services. Built with Spring Boot and other modern technologies, this platform ensures effective clinic management through a RESTful API.

name: irctc_backend_java
description: The IRCTC Backend Project is a Java based application designed to simulate a real-world train booking system. It supports user sign-up, login, fetching bookings, searching for trains, booking seats, and canceling bookings.

name: BookSummaries
description: Find in-depth cheat sheets for various technology and programming books. Topics cover microservices, system design, data engineering, coding best practices, machine learning, and more.

name: ordering-app
description: A scalable order management system built with NestJS and microservices. Features include order creation, tracking, and management with secure REST APIs, event-driven communication (RabbitMQ), and JWT-based authentication. Uses MongoDB for storage

name: bloggios-service-registry
description: Bloggios Service Registry, powered by Spring Boot and Discovery Server, centrally manages microservice instances. It enables dynamic discovery and registration, fostering seamless inter-service communication. This promotes scalability and resilience by updating instances in real-time for reliable system performance.

name: Billing_Invoice
description: This project consists of a backend microservice built with Node.js and a frontend application built with React. The system allows users to authenticate using Google OAuth, view their SaaS usage details, access billing information, and generate invoices based on cumulative usage. It also integrates with Zapier to automate billing processes.
